  "id": "05536c58-5053-5860-9810-d7f8ea7c678a",
  "slug": "banana-chips-recipe",
  "name": "How to Make Banana Chips",
  "recipe_type": "snack",
  "brief_description": "This is an easy way to make banana chips using raw banana and simple syrup.",
  "cuisine": null,
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "In a bowl, combine 2 tablespoons of water, turmeric powder, and salt. Mix well and set aside."
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Pour cooking oil in a wide pot and heat."
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "When the oil is hot, slice the bananas using a mandolin slicer and place a batch of sliced bananas in the hot oil."
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Deep fry the banana until almost crisp. When the bananas are almost done, scoop a teaspoon of the turmeric mixture and gently add to the oil. Note: Be very careful. This is an optional step. Doing this can add a yellowish color to the banana slices and make it more crisp."
    },
    {
      "position": 5,
      "text": "Once the oil stops bubbling, remove the bananas and drain excess oil. Set aside."
    },
    {
      "position": 6,
      "text": "Meanwhile, lets make the simple syrup. Heat a saucepan and pour in 1/2 cup of water and 1/2 cup sugar.Let boil."
    },
    {
      "position": 7,
      "text": "Gently stir the mixture and turn off the heat. Let cool."
    },
    {
      "position": 8,
      "text": "Quickly dip the banana chips in the simple syrup. Drain the excess liquid after dipping."
    },
    {
      "position": 9,
      "text": "Once the liquid dries-up, place the banana chips in a container, or serve right away."
    },
    {
      "position": 10,
      "text": "Share and enjoy!"
    }
  ],
  "servings": 8,
  "cooking_time_minutes": 15,
